==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Southdown
<hw>South"down`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to the South Downs, a range of pasture hills south of the Thames, in
England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Southdown sheep</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
celebrated breed of shortwooled, hornless sheep, highly valued on
account of the delicacy of their flesh. So called from the South Downs
where the breed originated.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Southdown</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Southdown
<hw>South"down`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A Southdown sheep.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1376 --></p>

<p><ent>Southeast</ent>⟦br⟧
